Design a premium, FAANG-level UX portfolio website for a Senior Product Designer named Thanushree Uppoor, based in Bangalore, with 5+ years of UX experience and 7.6+ years overall experience.

This portfolio should position her as a top-tier product designer specializing in enterprise systems, internal tools, and AI-powered platforms, with strong business impact and cross-functional leadership.

STYLE & VISUAL DIRECTION:
- Minimal, high-end, elegant (inspired by Google, Apple, Airbnb portfolios)
- Strong typography, lots of whitespace
- Neutral palette (black, white, grey, subtle accent)
- Grid-based layout, consistent spacing (8pt system)
- Clean, structured, not overly decorative
- Professional and mature (not trendy or flashy)

HERO SECTION:
- Name: Thanushree Uppoor
- Title: Senior Product Designer
- Tagline: Designing scalable enterprise systems and AI-driven platforms with measurable business impact
- Short intro: Product designer with 5+ years of UX experience, specializing in workflow-driven platforms, internal tools, and enterprise UX. Known for solving complex problems, improving operational efficiency, and delivering measurable outcomes.
- CTA: View Case Studies

SELECTED CASE STUDIES (3–4):
Create strong case study cards with:
- Project title
- Short problem statement
- Key metrics (highlight numbers)
- Role: Lead UX Designer
- Clean thumbnail

CASE STUDY 1:
Store Performance Platform & BI Dashboard
- Problem: Complex operational workflows and lack of centralized performance visibility across global teams
- Role: Lead UX Designer
- Work: Designed end-to-end enterprise BI platform from concept to high-fidelity
- Impact:
  - Improved task adherence by 30%
  - Reduced manager reporting time by 40–60%
  - Increased data completeness from 55% to 95%
  - Enabled $6.5M annual savings and $5M TCO reduction

CASE STUDY 2:
Organization Hierarchy & Navigation Platform (CTO Office)
- Problem: Difficult navigation and lack of clarity in large-scale organizational structure
- Work: Designed information architecture and navigation system for enterprise org restructuring
- Impact:
  - Improved navigation speed by 80%
  - Reduced person-finding time from 5 minutes to under 30 seconds
  - Increased onboarding clarity by 50%

CASE STUDY 3:
AI Image & Video Generation Platform
- Problem: Heavy reliance on external vendors and slow creative production cycles
- Work: Designed AI-powered platform for scalable content creation
- Impact:
  - Reduced production time
  - Enabled faster iteration across creative variations
  - Improved adoption of AI tools for non-technical users

CASE STUDY 4 (Optional):
Access Management Platform Redesign
- Problem: Complex permission systems causing confusion and errors
- Work: Simplified workflows and improved usability
- Impact:
  - Reduced access-related errors
  - Improved onboarding and system clarity

CASE STUDY PAGE TEMPLATE:
Each case study should follow FAANG storytelling:
1. Overview (role, duration, team)
2. Problem (clear business + user problem)
3. Constraints (enterprise complexity, stakeholders)
4. Research & Insights (user pain points, findings)
5. Design Process (flows, wireframes, iterations)
6. Solution (final UI, dashboards, workflows)
7. Impact (highlight metrics prominently)
8. Learnings

ABOUT SECTION:
- Strong professional story:
  “I design systems, not just screens. My work focuses on simplifying complex enterprise workflows and enabling teams to operate more efficiently at scale.”
- Experience highlights:
  - Senior UX Designer at Nike India Technology Centre
  - Previously Accenture and Wipro
  - Experience in enterprise platforms, internal tools, and AI systems
- Collaboration with Product, Engineering, Analytics, and Leadership
- Mentoring and design system contributions

SKILLS SECTION:
- UX & Product Design: Research, Interaction Design, Systems Thinking, Enterprise UX
- Process: Stakeholder management, Agile, Product thinking
- Tools: Figma, FigJam, Miro, Jira

DESIGN SYSTEM:
- Use reusable components
- Consistent spacing and typography
- Clean layout and alignment

FOOTER:
- Email
- LinkedIn
- Portfolio link

IMPORTANT:
- Emphasize measurable impact and metrics throughout
- Avoid generic UX language
- Make it feel like a senior, strategic designer portfolio
- Focus on clarity, structure, and storytelling
- Make it recruiter-friendly and easy to scan

OUTPUT:
Generate a complete portfolio layout including homepage and one detailed case study page.